- name: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism with or without anosmia
- type: disease
- source: MONDO_grouped
- details:
  - mondo_name: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism 7 with or without anosmia
  - group_name_bert: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism with or without anosmia
  - mondo_definition: A hypogonadotropic hypogonadism that has material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the GNRHR gene on chromosome 4q13, sometimes in association with mutation in another gene. No patients with anosmia have been reported.
  - umls_description: Diminution or cessation of secretion of one or more hormones from the anterior pituitary gland This may result from surgical or radiation ablation, non-secretory pituitary neoplasms, metastatic tumors, infarction, pituitary apoplexy, infiltrative or granulomatous processes, and other conditions.

